This SCP is very on-the-nose. It feels like a kind of meta-commentary while also explaining in-universe why D-Class are subjected to terrible things. It’s also a neat explanation and handwave for people who don’t LIKE D-Class as an element to be able to point towards and say , and combining all the older D-Class stereotypes into one place to basically make everyone win.

The Foundation, the O5s, the people who 'become' D-Class, researchers who need them, everyone.

I mean… well, it’s an overarching, deeply ingrained 'infection' creating test subjects, but eh. Silver linings.

In a way it’s a perfect entry for the contest.










